 teeth - but fruit bats defy that rule. I only recently learned that crocodilians eat significant amounts of plants, which makes them herbivores - I guess."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"score":1,"post_id":43746,"edited":false,"creation_date":1456736793,"comment_id":75903,"body":"@foaly Instead of making additional sections like <b>EDIT1<\/b> or <b>EDIT2<\/b> while retaining the original content, please <b>actually edit<\/b> the question so that it becomes short and precise."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a292721f76d95f73073719fbc53cec3d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":22186,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/22186/foaly","reputation":114,"display_name":"foaly"},"score":0,"post_id":43746,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/SjvUL.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":3340,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3340/wysiwyg","reputation":23153,"display_name":"WYSIWYG","accept_rate":80},"edited":false,"creation_date":1456738938,"comment_id":75905,"body":"@WYSIWYG For exactly that purpose I did not. The question is still correct and as precise as I can make it without wordy explanations. If anyone feels uncertain about it though, there is a clarification below in the edits. ;)"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d1c6641d5c8556d9f351765c89b510f6?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":19493,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19493/david-blomstrom","reputation":1247,"display_name":"David Blomstrom"},"score":3,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/210cc4a4b2f281aaffe0b26521fe1ab8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id