llow\">BLAST<\/a> from NCBI. Although it is not strictly a database in itself, it looks to align your sequence to similar sequences in external NCBI databases and quantifies the sequence similarity. It will reveal the species for you to go to a more appropriate database along with a lot of other information about the gene.<\/p>\n\n<p>There are plenty of parameters to alter to suit your specific needs, but generally, the default settings are a great place to start analysing your gene. You'll need to run a nucleotide test since you want to find the DNA sequence. The results might be difficult to interpret.<\/p>\n","answer_id":24519,"question_id":24516,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1456719929},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-8dhc5ulbBIw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAFA/HCK-pmE5M_s/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":10420,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10420/andrew","reputation":21,"display_name":"Andrew"},"score":2,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f437d9a11deebd214089822c26197f35?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3553,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3553/james","reputation":4533,"display_name":"James","accept_rate":83},"score":1,"post_id":24520,"edited":false,"creation_date":1417653896,"comment_id":39308,"body":"Although this does have the gene information (or at least information on where to access information on the genes) this is a protein centric database and deals in amino acid rather than nucleotide sequences."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-8dhc5ulbBIw/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAFA/HCK-pmE5M_s/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":10420,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10420/andrew","reputation":21,"display_name":"Andrew"},"score":1,"post_id":24520,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f437d9a11deebd214089822c26197f35?s=128&d